    Title: Simple version of mediation test for mediated moderation test

    med_mod.Rd

    The template of the monte carlo method in this function is from https://quantpsy.org/medmc/medmc.htm. This function can handle multi-level mediated moderation model where the moderator can be specified at either level one or two.

    med_mod(
  Model,
  iv = NULL,
  m = NULL,
  w = NULL,
  xw = NULL,
  dv = NULL,
  first_path = NULL,
  level_one_mod = TRUE,
  output = "Untitled",
  rep = 20000,
  conf = 95
)

    Arguments

    Model

    a list object containing the parameters of the model (from Mplus output file)

    iv

    the name of the independent variable

    m

    the name of the mediator

    w

    the name of the moderator

    xw

    the name of the interaction term

    dv

    the name of the dependent variable

    first_path

    the name of the first random path (should not be 'fixed')

    level_one_mod

    a binary variable indicating whether the moderation effect is on the first level (default: TRUE)

    output

    the name of the output image file (.png)

    rep

    the number of repetitions (default: 20000)

    conf

    the critical value used to generate confidence interval

    Value

    An image containing the distribution of the indirect effect and confidence interval
